      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why does Latvia require €42,500 insurance instead of €30,000?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Latvia set a higher insurance minimum for its Digital Nomad Visa program, likely to ensure nomads have adequate coverage and don't burden the public healthcare system. Always verify your policy meets this specific threshold—not just standard Schengen requirements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I renew the Latvia Digital Nomad Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The visa is valid for a maximum of 1 year and cannot be extended or renewed. After your year expires, you must leave Latvia for at least 180 days before you can apply again. This 6-month gap is enforced.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is SafetyWing accepted for Latvia's DNV?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, SafetyWing's coverage typically exceeds €42,500 (usually €250,000). However, verify your specific policy meets Latvia's requirement and keep documentation ready. Some applicants have been asked to provide specific confirmation of coverage limits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Latvia compare to Estonia for digital nomads?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Latvia is 20-30% cheaper than Estonia for similar living standards. Estonia has a stronger tech/startup scene and e-Residency program. Latvia is quieter with a smaller nomad community. Income requirements are similar (€2,857 vs €3,504), but Latvia has the higher insurance minimum.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel in the Schengen Area on Latvia's DNV?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Latvia is a Schengen member. Your temporary residence permit allows travel throughout the 27-country Schengen zone, making Europe very accessible from Riga.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does the Latvia DNV lead to permanent residency?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The Digital Nomad Visa is a temporary permit with no path to permanent residency. For long-term settlement in Latvia, you'd need to apply through different visa categories (employment, business, family ties).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
